Russia RTS Index Futures Rises on Improved Europe Debt Outlook

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-07-21T21:38:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/russia-rts-index-futures-rises-on-improved-europe-debt-outlook.html
Russia  RTS stock-index futures rose
for a fourth consecutive session as European leaders took steps
to halt the region’s debt crisis and crude rose to a one-month
high.  Futures on the dollar-denominated index expiring in
September advanced 0.3 percent to 197,180 yesterday. The gauge
has gained 4 percent since July 18.  Contracts on OAO Sberbank, Russia’s largest lender, gained
0.3 percent and those on OAO Rosneft, Russia’s biggest oil
producer, rose 0.2 percent. Futures on OAO Gazprom, the world’s
largest gas producer, advanced 0.3 percent.  European leaders empowered their 440-billion euro ($634
billion) rescue fund to buy debt across stressed euro nations
after eight hours of talks in Brussels. The fund can also aid
troubled banks and offer credit lines to repel speculators.
Leaders pledged a 160 billion euro aid package for  Greece , eased
the terms of its existing loans and cajoled bondholders into
footing part of the bill.  “Russia has been more exposed to global market sentiment
than other emerging markets, so a better picture in  Europe  would
certainly help Russia stocks,” said Eric Sohn, general partner
at North River Capital Partners, an emerging markets hedge fund
based in Sausalito, Calif. ‘Russia has been high-beta in terms
of global economic fears, so this could certainly be a boost.”  Crude for September delivery rose 73 cents to $99.13 a
barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange , the highest
settlement since June 14.  The euro rose to its highest against the dollar in two
weeks, rising 1.5 percent to $1.4425 at 5 p.m. in  New York . Some
investors buy dollar-denominated assets to protect value when
the dollar weakens against the euro and sell them when the
dollar gains.  U.S. stocks rose as Standard & Poor’s 500 Index gained 1.4
percent. The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  gained 1.6 percent to 1,729 in
Moscow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
